1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:03,104
Previously, on Lucifer...
My dad screwed us both.

2
00:00:03,137 --> 00:00:05,139
But perhaps there's a way

3
00:00:05,173 --> 00:00:06,640
for us to screw him back.
How?

4
00:00:06,674 --> 00:00:07,708
By killing you.

5
00:00:07,741 --> 00:00:09,677
Amenadiel's nice.
If he were nice,

6
00:00:09,710 --> 00:00:12,480
he wouldn't be sneaking around
behind my back with my friend,

7
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:13,481
and lying about it.

8
00:00:13,514 --> 00:00:15,149
You know, don't you?

9
00:00:15,183 --> 00:00:16,484
You're the ones
who have been

10
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,819
lying to me about
this fling for weeks.

11
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:20,054
I'd like to try and help.

12
00:00:20,088 --> 00:00:21,555
You don't have to treat me.

13
00:00:21,589 --> 00:00:23,357
I think I do.
For both of us.

14
00:00:23,391 --> 00:00:24,692
LUCIFER:
In my quest to help you die,

15
00:00:24,725 --> 00:00:26,094
I've done some research.

16
00:00:26,127 --> 00:00:27,428
I've read every book,

17
00:00:27,461 --> 00:00:28,629
I've analyzed every language.

18
00:00:28,662 --> 00:00:30,398
LUCIFER:
I'm completely out of ideas.

19
00:00:30,431 --> 00:00:31,499
We can't rewrite history.

20
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:33,634
Detective, you're a genius.

21
00:00:33,667 --> 00:00:35,336
You've just given me my idea.

22
00:00:36,737 --> 00:00:37,638
LUCIFER:
Once upon a time,

23
00:00:37,671 --> 00:00:41,409
there were two brothers--
Kane and Abel.

24
00:00:41,442 --> 00:00:45,213
They fought, as brothers often
do, over everything.

25
00:00:45,246 --> 00:00:47,215
What's that supposed to be?
Are we shaking hands

26
00:00:47,248 --> 00:00:48,716
or holding spiders?

27
00:00:48,749 --> 00:00:51,152
(chuckles)
That's you and your brother

28
00:00:51,185 --> 00:00:53,387
pummeling each other
over a pet rock.

29
00:00:53,421 --> 00:00:57,291
And here's you two scamps
tugging on both ends of a snake.

30
00:00:57,325 --> 00:00:58,492
That's not how it happened.

31
00:00:58,526 --> 00:01:00,728
Well, artistic license,
my friend.

32
00:01:00,761 --> 00:01:04,165
The point is that you were
always at each other's throats.

33
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:06,300
Until...
(sniffs)

34
00:01:06,334 --> 00:01:08,669
...you fought to the death.

35
00:01:08,702 --> 00:01:11,405
You killed Abel

36
00:01:11,439 --> 00:01:13,741
and became the world's

37
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:14,608
first murderer.

38
00:01:14,642 --> 00:01:17,111
Now, the part where
my father marks you,

39
00:01:17,145 --> 00:01:19,413
cursing you to walk the earth
for eternity,

40
00:01:19,447 --> 00:01:21,182
it's tricky to draw.
Now, um,

41
00:01:21,215 --> 00:01:23,251
I've heard this one before--
the ending sucks.

42
00:01:23,284 --> 00:01:24,885
My point exactly.

43
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:27,388
We all know how your story ends.

44
00:01:27,421 --> 00:01:31,392
But what if we change
how it begins?

45
00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:35,863
What if you never killed Abel?

46
00:01:35,896 --> 00:01:38,766
What if we did...

47
00:01:38,799 --> 00:01:40,234
this?

48
00:01:40,268 --> 00:01:41,435
Clean slate.

49
00:01:41,469 --> 00:01:43,271
That's impossible.
How would we do that?

50
00:01:43,304 --> 00:01:44,272
Oh, simple.

51
00:01:46,507 --> 00:01:48,142
I shall fly down to Hell,

52
00:01:48,176 --> 00:01:51,445
pluck your brother's soul, and
drop it into a vacant body.

53
00:01:51,479 --> 00:01:53,681
This would make Abel
technically alive,

54
00:01:53,714 --> 00:01:56,850
and therefore not murdered,
and you innocent.

55
00:01:56,884 --> 00:02:00,221
Wait, back up.
My brother is in Hell?

56
00:02:00,254 --> 00:02:02,290
Yes, of course.
In fact, he's our oldest tenant.

57
00:02:02,323 --> 00:02:05,493
I knew it. Do you know how many
times I've tried to tell people

58
00:02:05,526 --> 00:02:07,428
Abel is the asshat?
No one ever believes me.

59
00:02:07,461 --> 00:02:09,230
Right, can we just focus
on my genius plan?

60
00:02:09,263 --> 00:02:11,332
If we bring Abel
back to life,

61
00:02:11,365 --> 00:02:13,367
that would erase your crime.

62
00:02:13,401 --> 00:02:18,239
No crime, no mark,
no curse.

63
00:02:18,272 --> 00:02:21,775
You'd be mortal
and can finally die.

64
00:02:23,411 --> 00:02:24,745
PIERCE:
This one's good.

65
00:02:24,778 --> 00:02:27,781
Oh, this one's
even better.

66
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:29,717
Yeah, a bit past its
sell-by date, I'm afraid.

67
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,419
Wait till Abel
wakes up in this body.

68
00:02:31,452 --> 00:02:32,453
I never thought
I'd say this,

69
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:34,322
but slow down, Lieutenant.

70
00:02:34,355 --> 00:02:37,491
Time to lay down some
soul-dropping rules,

71
00:02:37,525 --> 00:02:39,193
or what I think the rules are,
at least.

72
00:02:39,227 --> 00:02:40,594
You have done this
before, right?

73
00:02:40,628 --> 00:02:44,698
Not exactly, but based
on a sample size of, uh,

74
00:02:44,732 --> 00:02:46,700
one crooked cop
and one goddess,

75
00:02:46,734 --> 00:02:49,837
I can only drop a soul into
someone who's recently died.

76
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:50,704
How recent?

77
00:02:50,738 --> 00:02:51,939
The instant after death.

78
00:02:51,972 --> 00:02:53,407
So we need a fresh one.

79
00:02:53,441 --> 00:02:54,542
How are we gonna find that?

80
00:02:54,575 --> 00:02:56,444
Hey, guys?

81
00:02:56,477 --> 00:02:58,346
There's been an explosion
at a high-rise downtown.

82
00:02:58,379 --> 00:03:00,548
There's one dead at the scene,
one on the way to the ICU.

83
00:03:00,581 --> 00:03:02,216
Oh, that's promising.

84
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:04,218
Excuse me?
PIERCE: He means
that's a promising chance

85
00:03:04,252 --> 00:03:05,619
to question the witness
at the hospital.

86
00:03:05,653 --> 00:03:06,620
Mm. Yes,

87
00:03:06,654 --> 00:03:09,290
where loads of people
are on the brink of death.

88
00:03:09,323 --> 00:03:12,593
So you want to question
someone who's unconscious

89
00:03:12,626 --> 00:03:14,628
and in critical condition?

90
00:03:14,662 --> 00:03:16,764
The witness may recover,
have some intel.

91
00:03:16,797 --> 00:03:18,432
Can't hurt to check.
Hmm.

92
00:03:18,466 --> 00:03:22,303
Okay, we'll work
the crime scene.

93
00:03:22,336 --> 00:03:24,538
Lucifer, you coming?

94
00:03:24,572 --> 00:03:26,974
Lucifer's coming with me
this time.

95
00:03:32,613 --> 00:03:33,981
Shall we?

96
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:36,550
* Such a pretty face

97
00:03:36,584 --> 00:03:38,586
* Straight teeth

98
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:40,921
* Look baby, now you playing
in a different league... *

99
00:03:40,954 --> 00:03:42,823
DAN: Bomb squad did
their threat report.

100
00:03:42,856 --> 00:03:44,858
Ruled it as a homicide,
handed it off to us.

101
00:03:44,892 --> 00:03:47,461
Looks like the bomb
came by messenger.

102
00:03:47,495 --> 00:03:49,897
And, uh, an assistant opened the
package, triggering the bomb.

103
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:52,533
Huh. Is that the messenger?

104
00:03:52,566 --> 00:03:54,968
Yep. Rest in peace, dude.

105
00:03:55,002 --> 00:03:57,805
We tried to track who sent it,
but they covered their tracks.

106
00:03:57,838 --> 00:03:59,006
One thing we do know

107
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,908
is that the assistant
wasn't the target.

108
00:04:00,941 --> 00:04:02,142
Package was addressed
to her boss.

109
00:04:02,175 --> 00:04:06,914
Producer Alexa Lee, she just
came in, she's pretty shook up.

110
00:04:06,947 --> 00:04:08,882
All right.
Let's go talk to her.

111
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,585
Where were you
when the blast occurred?

112
00:04:11,619 --> 00:04:12,786
At home.

113
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,054
My Tuesday
session with Paolo,

114
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,489
my Pilates trainer.

115
00:04:15,523 --> 00:04:17,558
You have any idea
who'd want to hurt you?

116
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:20,428
Any past enemies, grudges,
anything like that?

117
00:04:20,461 --> 00:04:22,330
How much time you got?
(scoffs)

118
00:04:22,363 --> 00:04:24,031
Come on, this is Hollywood.

119
00:04:24,064 --> 00:04:26,367
I get way more hate
mail than fan mail.

120
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:29,637
Did any one threat
stand out at all?

121
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:31,639
Uh, my assistant will know.

122
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:32,906
Bree Garland.

123
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:35,409
She deals with all my mail
and...

124
00:04:35,443 --> 00:04:36,910
oh, my God,
did Bree open the box?

125
00:04:36,944 --> 00:04:38,546
She's in the ICU.

126
00:04:38,579 --> 00:04:39,947
But we haven't heard word yet.

127
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,582
Oh, no.

128
00:04:41,615 --> 00:04:42,883
It should have been me.

129
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:44,818
Poor Bree.

130
00:04:44,852 --> 00:04:46,019
LUCIFER:
Bree Garland?

131
00:04:46,053 --> 00:04:48,456
She won't do at all.
Why not?

132
00:04:48,489 --> 00:04:50,023
Well, how much
do you hate your brother

133
00:04:50,057 --> 00:04:52,526
on a scale of one to ten?

134
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,962
One thousand, infinity plus one.

135
00:04:54,995 --> 00:04:57,398
Right, well, if we pop Abel
into a body this young,

136
00:04:57,431 --> 00:04:59,533
you could be stuck with him
for another 70 years.

137
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:01,001
That's a lot of quality time.

138
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:01,969
Copy, not her.

139
00:05:02,002 --> 00:05:04,972
(sighs) No, what we need
is someone ancient,

140
00:05:05,005 --> 00:05:06,640
someone at death's door.

141
00:05:06,674 --> 00:05:09,910
-(heart rate monitor flatlining)
-Someone...

142
00:05:15,082 --> 00:05:17,418
(clears throat)

143
00:05:26,894 --> 00:05:28,429
PIERCE:
"Do not resuscitate.

144
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:30,431
"97 years old,

145
00:05:30,464 --> 00:05:31,565
no next of kin."

146
00:05:31,599 --> 00:05:33,066
Perfect.

147
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,936
Yes, we'll put Abel
in this old coot. (giggles)

148
00:05:35,969 --> 00:05:38,005
He gets a second
chance at life

149
00:05:38,038 --> 00:05:39,640
and you get your chance
at death.

150
00:05:39,673 --> 00:05:41,442
Let's do this.

151
00:05:41,475 --> 00:05:42,743
Right.

152
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,782
Enjoy the show, Dad.

153
00:05:48,816 --> 00:05:50,451
(wings whoosh)

154
00:05:55,623 --> 00:05:58,626
(heart rate monitor flatlining)

155
00:05:58,659 --> 00:06:00,528
-(wind whooshes)
-(feet thud)

156
00:06:00,561 --> 00:06:02,563
Right.

157
00:06:05,132 --> 00:06:08,702
(heart rate monitor
beats rhythmically)

158
00:06:08,736 --> 00:06:10,137
(sighs)

159
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:11,539
Any second now.

160
00:06:14,642 --> 00:06:17,611
Any second.

161
00:06:17,645 --> 00:06:19,046
You sure you did this right?

162
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:20,414
Well, I know I grabbed Abel
down below.

163
00:06:20,448 --> 00:06:22,750
PIERCE: Did you put him
in the right place?
LUCIFER: Probably.

164
00:06:22,783 --> 00:06:23,717
PIERCE: What do you
mean, "probably"?

165
00:06:23,751 --> 00:06:25,519
LUCIFER: Well, like
I said, I'm new to this.

166
00:06:25,553 --> 00:06:26,687
But where else would
I have dropped him?

167
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:29,089
Did you screw this up?
I don't know.

168
00:06:29,122 --> 00:06:30,924
I mean, it's not like
there's an instruction manual.

169
00:06:35,629 --> 00:06:37,064
Lucifer.

170
00:06:37,097 --> 00:06:38,499
Where did she go?

171
00:06:38,532 --> 00:06:39,533
Hmm?

172
00:06:47,007 --> 00:06:49,109
Oh.

173
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:51,845
Okay, I see
what's happened here.

174
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:54,848
It appears I may have misplaced
your brother's soul.

175
00:06:54,882 --> 00:06:56,049
(chuckles)

176
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:57,150
But in my defense,
what were the chances

177
00:06:57,184 --> 00:07:00,854
of this young lady expiring
at the exact same time?

178
00:07:00,888 --> 00:07:02,590
Tell me you didn't
put Abel in her body.

179
00:07:02,623 --> 00:07:04,658
(sighs) So I make
one teeny mistake.

180
00:07:04,692 --> 00:07:07,194
Yes, it appears that Abel is
running around as a young woman.

181
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:10,030
But the point is, we did it.

182
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:12,099
Abel's alive.

183
00:07:12,132 --> 00:07:14,702
What matters is,
your curse is lifted

184
00:07:14,735 --> 00:07:16,737
and you should no longer
have your mark.

185
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:18,472
So come on,
let's have a look.

186
00:07:18,506 --> 00:07:22,476
The mark is still there,
which means I'm still cursed.

187
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:25,045
We failed.

188
00:07:28,582 --> 00:07:30,117
(sighs)

189
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:31,585
Bugger.

190
00:07:31,619 --> 00:07:33,621
*

191
00:07:40,928 --> 00:07:43,163
*

192
00:07:49,837 --> 00:07:51,905
(scoffs)

193
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:53,641
He's a spry one.

194
00:07:53,674 --> 00:07:55,008
Or she.

195
00:07:55,042 --> 00:07:56,577
No sign of her anywhere.

196
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:57,845
I mean, him.

197
00:07:57,878 --> 00:07:59,079
This is head-spinning,
isn't it?

198
00:07:59,112 --> 00:08:01,081
We need to find him.
Why?

199
00:08:01,114 --> 00:08:02,783
You already figured
out a plan "B"?

200
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:04,852
Another way Abel can help
remove your curse? What is it?

201
00:08:04,885 --> 00:08:06,854
I don't know, but whatever it
is, it has to involve Abel.

202
00:08:06,887 --> 00:08:07,921
Right.

203
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:09,156
Time to call
the detective.

204
00:08:09,189 --> 00:08:10,090
Yeah, that's a great idea.

205
00:08:10,123 --> 00:08:12,192
"Hey, Decker.
We broke Abel out of Hell,

206
00:08:12,225 --> 00:08:13,594
"dropped his soul
into the wrong body

207
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:15,195
"and lost him.
Now he's on the lam

208
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:16,530
"in the body of the victim
from your case.

209
00:08:16,564 --> 00:08:18,832
Also, I'm immortal."

210
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,634
There's no need to get snippy.

211
00:08:20,668 --> 00:08:22,803
Fine, we'll do this on
our own under the radar.

212
00:08:22,836 --> 00:08:23,904
Now, he's your brother.

213
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:25,138
Where do you think he'd go?

214
00:08:25,172 --> 00:08:26,707
I don't know,
we're not exactly in touch.

215
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,741
It's been a few millenia.

216
00:08:27,775 --> 00:08:29,076
You tortured him in Hell.

217
00:08:29,109 --> 00:08:30,911
You probably know him
better than I do.

218
00:08:30,944 --> 00:08:32,245
(sighs)
Barely saw him, actually.

219
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:34,615
I was more of a big
picture kind of guy.

220
00:08:34,648 --> 00:08:37,751
The good news is
I do know a demon or two.

221
00:08:37,785 --> 00:08:39,219
Come on.

222
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:41,121
CHLOE:
Who knew a producer

223
00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:43,657
could have this many enemies?

224
00:08:43,691 --> 00:08:46,594
Occupational hazard,
I guess.

225
00:08:46,627 --> 00:08:48,061
Yikes, check this out.

226
00:08:48,095 --> 00:08:49,262
Look at that.

227
00:08:49,296 --> 00:08:51,331
Huh.

228
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:52,766
"You're going to die."

229
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,768
Hmm.
I do believe
we have a winner.

230
00:08:54,802 --> 00:08:58,305
Hang on.

231
00:08:58,338 --> 00:08:59,973
Look at the Gs.

232
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:01,642
It's the same handwriting.

233
00:09:01,675 --> 00:09:02,876
Sent a few weeks back.

234
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:04,144
They were upset

235
00:09:04,177 --> 00:09:06,279
about one of Alexa's movies,
The Plunge.

236
00:09:06,313 --> 00:09:08,782
"It's full of lies.

237
00:09:08,816 --> 00:09:11,885
If you want the real truth,
read The Z Prophecy."

238
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:12,886
What is that?

239
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,254
Wait, Alexa made The Plunge?

240
00:09:14,287 --> 00:09:15,088
Have you seen it?

241
00:09:15,122 --> 00:09:17,290
(chuckling):
Oh, man. A group of teens,

242
00:09:17,324 --> 00:09:18,859
they have to travel
to the center of the Earth

243
00:09:18,892 --> 00:09:20,227
to unclog
this blocked-up magma.

244
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:21,294
Oh, man, does it get intense.

245
00:09:21,328 --> 00:09:23,363
Mm-hmm. Whoever
wrote this letter

246
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:26,767
wants people to read
The Z Prophecy.

247
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,235
Wonder what it is.

248
00:09:28,268 --> 00:09:30,804
DAN: "Visionary, Liam Wade,"
author of The Z Prophecy

249
00:09:30,838 --> 00:09:33,874
and a whole bunch of other
conspiracy theories. Wow.

250
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:36,009
Seems pretty bonkers.
Check out his manifesto.

251
00:09:36,043 --> 00:09:37,911
CHLOE:
Look.

252
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,783
It's the same handwriting
as the letters.

253
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:44,251
Okay, we need to talk to him

254
00:09:44,284 --> 00:09:46,920
and find out exactly why
he was threatening Alexa.

255
00:09:46,954 --> 00:09:48,021
CHARLOTTE:
Crap.

256
00:09:48,055 --> 00:09:50,190
Old socks.

257
00:09:50,223 --> 00:09:51,659
Moldy leaves.

258
00:09:51,692 --> 00:09:53,827
If it tastes so bad,
why drink it?

259
00:09:53,861 --> 00:09:55,162
