00:20:12,779 --> 00:20:14,414
Listen, Abel wanted
to kill me just as much

524
00:20:14,447 --> 00:20:15,682
as I wanted to kill him.

525
00:20:15,715 --> 00:20:17,284
Why do you think he's in Hell?

526
00:20:17,317 --> 00:20:19,819
I'm just the guy
who won the fight.

527
00:20:21,521 --> 00:20:23,290
Hello.

528
00:20:23,323 --> 00:20:25,558
Where would I
and therefore Abel go next?

529
00:20:25,592 --> 00:20:27,594
Wherever she's going.

530
00:20:29,962 --> 00:20:31,298
(Kane sighs)

531
00:20:31,331 --> 00:20:33,533
* Well, I got
to keep on walking *

532
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:36,035
* Yeah, I'm looking
for a phonograph *

533
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,837
* That'll play out loud...

534
00:20:39,439 --> 00:20:41,408
Results from our samples
came back.

535
00:20:41,441 --> 00:20:43,276
Liam told the truth.

536
00:20:43,310 --> 00:20:45,412
No trace of explosive compounds
on the farm.

537
00:20:45,445 --> 00:20:46,746
Or much else.
Hmm.

538
00:20:46,779 --> 00:20:48,047
Unless you count
all the turkey jerky

539
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,782
he was hoarding
for the apocalypse.

540
00:20:49,816 --> 00:20:51,784
(chuckles)

541
00:20:51,818 --> 00:20:53,653
"Bolivian crime organizations"?

542
00:20:53,686 --> 00:20:55,588
You're not taking Liam
seriously, are you?

543
00:20:55,622 --> 00:20:57,290
Okay, don't laugh,
but I've been looking into

544
00:20:57,324 --> 00:20:58,391
some of his theories.

545
00:20:58,425 --> 00:21:00,393
Ring of evil carnies.

546
00:21:00,427 --> 00:21:01,761
I'm calling it.

547
00:21:01,794 --> 00:21:02,895
(both chuckle)

548
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:04,931
All right. Ella got back to me
with her bomb report.

549
00:21:04,964 --> 00:21:06,899
It was made from fertilizer
that's banned in the U.S.,

550
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,435
but guess where
it's still being used.

551
00:21:08,468 --> 00:21:09,836
Bolivia? No way.

552
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:11,538
Yeah. So I took a closer
look into Alexa's company

553
00:21:11,571 --> 00:21:13,840
to see if I could prove
a Bolivian connection.

554
00:21:13,873 --> 00:21:15,408
Uh-huh.

555
00:21:15,442 --> 00:21:17,910
She's got a lot
of international financiers,

556
00:21:17,944 --> 00:21:19,946
which is pretty normal nowadays.

557
00:21:19,979 --> 00:21:21,848
But I highlighted
the Bolivian ones.

558
00:21:21,881 --> 00:21:23,983
Guess there was a grain of truth
in Liam's craziness.

559
00:21:24,016 --> 00:21:27,387
We should cross-check that list
with the FBI and DHS.

560
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:29,389
I already did.
These names are linked up

561
00:21:29,422 --> 00:21:30,823
to the Bolivian drug cartel.

562
00:21:30,857 --> 00:21:32,659
(computer chiming)

563
00:21:32,692 --> 00:21:34,927
This is my contact from the TSA.

564
00:21:37,764 --> 00:21:40,767
One of the Bolivian contractors
landed in L.A. this morning.

565
00:21:41,868 --> 00:21:43,703
Wonder what he's doing here.

566
00:21:46,939 --> 00:21:48,641
I know you can do it, Abel.

567
00:21:53,446 --> 00:21:54,447
(chuckles)

568
00:21:54,481 --> 00:21:57,750
Wait. Who are you?

569
00:21:58,985 --> 00:22:00,653
How do you know all of this?

570
00:22:01,921 --> 00:22:02,922
No!
(gunshot)

571
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:04,424
That's her.

572
00:22:04,457 --> 00:22:05,558
(onlookers screaming)

573
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,399
What are you
doing here?

574
00:22:12,432 --> 00:22:14,501
Where'd he go? I mean,
where did she go?

575
00:22:14,534 --> 00:22:15,802
I don't know.

576
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:16,869
(sighs)

577
00:22:21,774 --> 00:22:24,477
I told you
to stay out of my way.

578
00:22:24,511 --> 00:22:26,446
And I told you
Father cursed Kane for a reason.

579
00:22:26,479 --> 00:22:28,781
You actually thought
that I would just

580
00:22:28,815 --> 00:22:31,651
sit around while you two idiots

581
00:22:31,684 --> 00:22:33,386
were raising Abel?

582
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:34,687
I've been following you, Luci.

583
00:22:35,822 --> 00:22:37,590
So reckless,
even by your standards.

584
00:22:37,624 --> 00:22:39,892
(chuckles) Well, I think
it's rather brilliant, actually.

585
00:22:39,926 --> 00:22:43,029
Using the wings Dad
unfairly punished me with

586
00:22:43,062 --> 00:22:45,598
to undo another one
of his unfair punishments.

587
00:22:45,632 --> 00:22:46,933
Do you seriously not realize

588
00:22:46,966 --> 00:22:48,668
just how dangerous it is
to anger Father?

589
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:49,902
(scoffs)

590
00:22:49,936 --> 00:22:52,405
Have you also forgotten that
He took away your devil face?

591
00:22:52,439 --> 00:22:54,407
Precisely my point, brother.

592
00:22:54,441 --> 00:22:56,042
I've got nothing left to lose.

593
00:22:56,075 --> 00:22:58,678
Oh, don't be foolish, Luci.

594
00:22:58,711 --> 00:23:00,179
There are so many things

595
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:01,948
that Father can still
take away from you.

596
00:23:01,981 --> 00:23:03,950
Again with the fearmongering.

597
00:23:03,983 --> 00:23:07,920
For the nth time, I'm not going
to just take Dad's abuse.

598
00:23:07,954 --> 00:23:10,189
Cowering from Him
is your jam, remember?

599
00:23:10,222 --> 00:23:12,759
You know what?

600
00:23:12,792 --> 00:23:16,963
It's not you that I am trying
to prove my worth to.

601
00:23:16,996 --> 00:23:19,666
So think what you will,
do what you will.

602
00:23:19,699 --> 00:23:22,835
I'm gonna find Abel and send him
back to where he belongs.

603
00:23:24,471 --> 00:23:25,505
Oh, so we're just gonna
let him leave,

604
00:23:25,538 --> 00:23:26,639
so he can get in our way later.

605
00:23:26,673 --> 00:23:28,841
No, no.

606
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,042
Next time, we'll be ready.

607
00:23:30,076 --> 00:23:32,111
Bad news. Dead guy?

608
00:23:32,144 --> 00:23:33,780
Bolivian cartel hit man.

609
00:23:33,813 --> 00:23:34,747
What?

610
00:23:34,781 --> 00:23:38,017
The Bolivian cartel
wants to kill Bree? Why?

611
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:39,118
Don't know.

612
00:23:39,151 --> 00:23:41,688
(sighs) There's no keeping this
from Decker anymore.

613
00:23:41,721 --> 00:23:43,790
Fine. I'll let you tell her.

614
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:50,530
Okay.

615
00:23:50,563 --> 00:23:53,232
Okay? That's it?

616
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:55,502
What, you're not gonna
tear him a new one?

617
00:23:55,535 --> 00:23:57,604
Come on, I've gotten
much worse for much less.

618
00:23:57,637 --> 00:23:59,472
I'm not gonna yell at my boss,

619
00:23:59,506 --> 00:24:02,675
even if he lost
our witness twice.

620
00:24:02,709 --> 00:24:05,011
Oh, because you've got
a soft spot for him?

621
00:24:05,044 --> 00:24:06,813
Because I'm not an idiot.

622
00:24:06,846 --> 00:24:09,782
Look, you're the lieutenant,
you call the shots.

623
00:24:09,816 --> 00:24:12,051
But the next time you want
to steal my partner

624
00:24:12,084 --> 00:24:14,654
to tail the target
of my investigation,

625
00:24:14,687 --> 00:24:16,088
you want to clue me in first?

626
00:24:16,122 --> 00:24:18,525
Before it turns into
a public gunfight?

627
00:24:18,558 --> 00:24:20,092
Deal. Next time.

628
00:24:20,126 --> 00:24:22,094
You said "target."

629
00:24:22,128 --> 00:24:24,697
Are you thinking the bomb was
meant for Bree and not Alexa?

630
00:24:24,731 --> 00:24:26,666
Well, maybe the Bolivians knew

631
00:24:26,699 --> 00:24:28,000
that Bree always opened
her boss' mail,

632
00:24:28,034 --> 00:24:29,569
used it as a misdirect.

633
00:24:29,602 --> 00:24:30,770
Well, I still
don't understand.

634
00:24:30,803 --> 00:24:33,873
Why does the Bolivian cartel
want a Hollywood assistant dead?

635
00:24:33,906 --> 00:24:35,808
Did she neglect
to pick the pistachios

636
00:24:35,842 --> 00:24:36,909
off their quinoa salad?

637
00:24:36,943 --> 00:24:37,844
Well, that's the missing piece.

638
00:24:37,877 --> 00:24:39,979
So we should find out
what Alexa knows.

639
00:24:40,012 --> 00:24:42,882
If I can have my partner back?
Of course.

640
00:24:42,915 --> 00:24:44,784
I'll track down Bree,
I need to find him before...

641
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:45,818
You mean her.

642
00:24:45,852 --> 00:24:50,590
I need to find her
before the cartel does.

643
00:24:50,623 --> 00:24:52,892
Mm-hmm.

644
00:24:58,665 --> 00:25:00,633
So the bomb
wasn't for me.

645
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:01,834
Well, the intended target

646
00:25:01,868 --> 00:25:04,303
was your assistant, Bree.
Have you heard from her lately?

647
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,539
What are you talking about?
Bree's in the hospital.

648
00:25:06,573 --> 00:25:07,674
She fled from the ER.

649
00:25:07,707 --> 00:25:09,809
No one's heard from her.
She could be in a lot of danger.

650
00:25:09,842 --> 00:25:11,077
I guarantee she is.

651
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:13,580
Well, how's that
possible?

652
00:25:13,613 --> 00:25:16,015
I-I was told she suffered
fatal internal injuries.

653
00:25:16,048 --> 00:25:19,018
Yes, well, you could say
she's like a new man.

654
00:25:19,051 --> 00:25:19,886
(Alexa sighs)

655
00:25:19,919 --> 00:25:22,655
Well, thank God,
but we need to find her.

656
00:25:22,689 --> 00:25:25,191
We're doing everything we can
to make sure she's safe.

657
00:25:25,224 --> 00:25:27,560
What?
Oh, yes, yes, of course.

658
00:25:27,594 --> 00:25:29,696
That, too,
but I need her back so bad.

659
00:25:29,729 --> 00:25:31,964
Do you know what it's like
to have someone take away

660
00:25:31,998 --> 00:25:33,232
an assistant you depend on?

661
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:35,134
Yes, I do, actually.
(sighs)

662
00:25:35,167 --> 00:25:37,937
I mean, I-I am seriously
lost here without her.

663
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,972
I-I don't even know how
to call out of the office.

664
00:25:40,006 --> 00:25:40,873
Do you know how?

665
00:25:40,907 --> 00:25:43,042
So you have no idea
what kind of beef

666
00:25:43,075 --> 00:25:45,945
these Bolivian associates
of yours may have had with Bree?

667
00:25:45,978 --> 00:25:47,246
I don't.

668
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:48,715
Bree is fluent in Spanish,

669
00:25:48,748 --> 00:25:50,583
so she dealt with those
investors directly.

670
00:25:50,617 --> 00:25:52,351
And you didn't think
to vet them at all

671
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:53,586
before you went
into business with them?

672
00:25:53,620 --> 00:25:56,756
Have you seen the films I make?
I can't afford to be picky.

673
00:25:56,789 --> 00:25:58,725
Someone offers me money,
I take it.

674
00:25:58,758 --> 00:26:01,060
Okay, well, I'm gonna need to
see any documented interactions

675
00:26:01,093 --> 00:26:02,128
you have with these investors.

676
00:26:02,161 --> 00:26:04,697
Absolutely, they're in there.
Okay.

677
00:26:09,769 --> 00:26:11,037
Oh, right.

678
00:26:12,639 --> 00:26:15,107
Only Bree's fingerprint
can unlock it.

679
00:26:15,141 --> 00:26:17,877
Bree installed a biometric lock
on the file cabinet?

680
00:26:17,910 --> 00:26:19,178
Seems a little paranoid.

681
00:26:19,211 --> 00:26:21,080
What did she
have to hide?

682
00:26:22,949 --> 00:26:25,384
Two recent incoming wires
for 50 grand each,

683
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:27,119
both from a South
American bank.
Bingo.

684
00:26:27,153 --> 00:26:29,188
Shady side business
with the Bolivians it is.

685
00:26:29,221 --> 00:26:32,224
So Bree was embezzling
from that useless boss of hers.

686
00:26:32,258 --> 00:26:33,693
Huh, who can blame her?

687
00:26:33,726 --> 00:26:35,962
Does loyalty mean
nothing to you?

688
00:26:35,995 --> 00:26:38,631
Alexa gave Bree
her first job in Hollywood.

689
00:26:38,665 --> 00:26:39,766
She trained her.

690
00:26:39,799 --> 00:26:41,834
You don't just
ditch that

691
00:26:41,868 --> 00:26:44,804
the minute some
big-armed, blue-eyed,

692
00:26:44,837 --> 00:26:45,638
toned...

693
00:26:45,672 --> 00:26:48,775
Bolivian drug lord
comes around, okay?

694
00:26:48,808 --> 00:26:49,876
Y-you, you don't, you don't.

695
00:26:49,909 --> 00:26:52,011
Dan, if Bree bolted from the ER,

696
00:26:52,044 --> 00:26:53,980
maybe she left some things
behind, like her phone.

697
00:26:54,013 --> 00:26:56,315
Mm-hmm, which could hold proof

698
00:26:56,348 --> 00:26:58,150
to her connection
with the Bolivians.

699
00:26:58,184 --> 00:26:59,886
That's good thinking.
I'm gonna check on that.

700
00:26:59,919 --> 00:27:00,920
Okay, thanks.

701
00:27:00,953 --> 00:27:02,121
All right,
I'm gonna see if Pierce

702
00:27:02,154 --> 00:27:03,222
had any luck finding Bree.

703
00:27:03,255 --> 00:27:05,024
Oh, well,
he won't need any luck.

704
00:27:05,057 --> 00:27:06,893
He's got something
far better than that.

705
00:27:06,926 --> 00:27:09,328
Decker's right. You're cute.

706
00:27:09,361 --> 00:27:12,765
But I'm mid-bounty
and I just got a lead.

707
00:27:12,799 --> 00:27:13,966
So, if you don't mind...

708
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,302
Lucifer told me to tell you
this is exactly the opposite

709
00:27:16,335 --> 00:27:18,237
of what Amenadiel wants.

710
00:27:18,270 --> 00:27:20,139
I'm in.

711
00:27:20,172 --> 00:27:22,141
Great.

712
00:27:22,174 --> 00:27:23,876
How do we find him?
Well...

713
00:27:23,910 --> 00:27:27,246
Your brother's
a predictable one.

714
00:27:27,279 --> 00:27:30,316
He always runs to food or boobs.

715
00:27:30,349 --> 00:27:31,784
Usually boobs.

716
00:27:31,818 --> 00:27:33,319
That's how we found him
the first time.

717
00:27:33,352 --> 00:27:36,022
Now he has boobs, that might
change his itinerary.

718
00:27:36,055 --> 00:27:38,124
That's right,
I totally forgot about that.

719
00:27:38,157 --> 00:27:40,827
(chuckles) Is he hot?

720
00:27:40,860 --> 00:27:43,229
Just tell me how we find him.

721
00:27:43,262 --> 00:27:44,330
Well, every now and again,

722
00:27:44,363 --> 00:27:47,366
the sucker would do something
I never saw coming.

723
00:27:47,399 --> 00:27:48,968
(elevator bell dings)

724
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:50,136
Hello, Kane.

725
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:51,904
And good-bye.
(gunshot)

726
00:27:51,938 --> 00:27:53,239
(groans)

727
00:27:56,876 --> 00:27:58,144
Just like that.

728
00:28:02,782 --> 00:28:04,250
Yes! (grunts) Finally!

729
00:28:04,283 --> 00:28:05,384
Slayed you before

730
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:07,319
you slayed me! (grunts)

731
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:08,755
Ashes to ashes,

732
00:28:08,788 --> 00:28:10,456
you bastard!

733
00:28:10,489 --> 00:28:12,324
(grunts rhythmically)

734
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:14,961
Enjoy it while
it lasts, Abel.

735
00:28:14,994 --> 00:28:17,296
How do you know my name?

736
00:28:17,329 --> 00:28:18,931
And what is that
supposed to mean?

737
00:28:20,299 --> 00:28:21,433
(grunting)

738
00:28:29,408 --> 00:28:30,576
Thanks for the heads-up.

739
00:28:30,609 --> 00:28:33,946
You said you wanted to die.
Make up your mind, cupcake.

740
00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:35,848
And the mark is still there.

741
00:28:35,882 --> 00:28:38,350
(sobbing) Please, no.
No, please.

742
00:28:38,384 --> 00:28:39,852
Please.

743
00:28:39,886 --> 00:28:42,421
Just make it quick, Kane.
Please make it quick.

744
00:28:44,523 --> 00:28:46,425
No.

745
00:28:46,458 --> 00:28:49,328
I need you alive,
so you can help me die.

746
00:28:49,361 --> 00:28:52,298
Wait, what?

747
00:28:52,331 --> 00:28:54,400
This has to be a trick.
You always kill me.

748
00:28:54,433 --> 00:28:56,302
That was when you were in Hell,

749
00:28:56,335 --> 00:28:58,437
where you've spent
the last few millennia.

750
00:28:58,470 --> 00:29:00,940
Maze tortured you
in the afterlife.

751
00:29:00,973 --> 00:29:03,943
Your punishment
was to get killed

752
00:29:03,976 --> 00:29:06,813
by me, over and over.

753
00:29:06,846 --> 00:29:08,380
MAZE:
That's right.

754
00:29:08,414 --> 00:29:10,783
You were trapped in a Hell loop,
but now you're out.

755
00:29:12,518 --> 00:29:15,021
You're alive, brother.

756
00:29:16,889 --> 00:29:18,490
(imitates explosion)

757
00:29:22,061 --> 00:29:23,529
Turns out Abel killing me
didn't remove the mark.

758
00:29:23,562 --> 00:29:25,497
Mm-hmm. Right, yes,
I got that from the whole

759
00:29:25,531 --> 00:29:27,033
"you still being alive"
of it all.

760
00:29:27,066 --> 00:29:29,969
So much for making
everything even-steven.

761
00:29:30,002 --> 00:29:31,370
It's now time for Plan "C."

762
00:29:31,403 --> 00:29:33,339
(scoffs)
I didn't realize we had one.

763
00:29:33,372 --> 00:29:35,007
We don't.

764
00:29:35,041 --> 00:29:36,909
But we'll think of something.

765
00:29:36,943 --> 00:29:38,544
Okay, and how is bringing
your she-brother

766
00:29:38,577 --> 00:29:40,312
into the precinct
going to help?

767
00:29:40,346 --> 00:29:43,382
Much as I'm enjoying his
Basic Instinct routine.

768
00:29:43,415 --> 00:29:44,951
First things first,
we have to make sure

769
00:29:44,984 --> 00:29:46,052
the Bolivians
don't kill him.

770
00:29:48,054 --> 00:29:49,021
Bree.

771
00:29:49,055 --> 00:29:51,457
I'm Detective Decker.

772
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:54,360
This is Charlotte Richards
from the DA's office.

773
00:29:54,393 --> 00:29:55,394
Miss Garland,
do you confirm

774
00:29:55,427 --> 00:29:57,997
that you're waiving
your right to legal council?

775
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:02,068
Yes. Woman, I will waive
whatever you want me to waive.

776
00:30:04,971 --> 00:30:06,839
Uh, Lieutenant said
he had noticed

777
00:30:06,873 --> 00:30:08,440
some PTSD symptoms,

778
00:30:08,474 --> 00:30:09,508
so we should just
kind of roll with it

779
00:30:09,541 --> 00:30:11,844
if we can.

780
00:30:11,878 --> 00:30:14,546
Don't take this lightly,
Miss Garland.

781
00:30:14,580 --> 00:30:16,015
It's a big decision.

782
00:30:16,048 --> 00:30:19,051
Mmm. Not as big as my flock.

783
00:30:19,085 --> 00:30:21,487
Do you know how many
sheep I possess?

784
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:24,356
Enough for two wives.

785
00:30:24,390 --> 00:30:27,093
Enough to feed
our offspring

786
00:30:27,126 --> 00:30:29,495
and our offspring's offspring.

787
00:30:29,528 --> 00:30:30,496
LUCIFER:
He fits right in.

788
00:30:30,529 --> 00:30:33,032
Is it me, or is your plan
going down in flames?

789
00:30:33,065 --> 00:30:34,366
It'll work.

790
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:37,369
Well, as impressive
as your flock sounds,

791
00:30:37,403 --> 00:30:38,905
let's get back
to the deal.

792
00:30:38,938 --> 00:30:41,440
The terms are simple.

793
00:30:41,473 --> 00:30:42,508
You share all the
information you have

794
00:30:42,541 --> 00:30:45,077
on the Bolivian cartel
in exchange for immunity.

795
00:30:45,111 --> 00:30:47,046
And the full protection
of the LAPD.

796
00:30:47,079 --> 00:30:49,548
Yes, to whatever
those words mean.

797
00:30:49,581 --> 00:30:53,519
Now, let's discuss who is going
to lay with me first.

798
00:30:53,552 --> 00:30:57,556
Uh, don't you want to read
the terms of the deal, at least?

799
00:30:57,589 --> 00:31:00,960
What for? I've been told
you're very wise.

800
00:31:00,993 --> 00:31:02,528
I trust you.

801
00:31:02,561 --> 00:31:03,662
CHARLOTTE:
Just like that?

802
00:31:03,695 --> 00:31:05,464
You're going to
let us drive this,

803
00:31:05,497 --> 00:31:07,566
just completely give up control?

804
00:31:07,599 --> 00:31:08,567
Mm-hmm.

805
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,502
Doesn't that scare you?

806
00:31:10,536 --> 00:31:14,506
Not nearly as much as the place
I just escaped.

807
00:31:14,540 --> 00:31:17,643
I would do anything to avoid
returning to that Hell.

808
00:31:17,676 --> 00:31:19,878
If you'd been there,
you would do the same.

809
00:31:24,984 --> 00:31:25,952
Charlotte.

810
00:31:25,985 --> 00:31:28,454
Yes, sorry,
we're good.

811
00:31:28,487 --> 00:31:31,557
Great. Great.
Okay, Bree?

812
00:31:31,590 --> 00:31:33,092
Mm-hmm.
Come on, you're
coming with me.

813
00:31:33,125 --> 00:31:36,528
(sharp inhale)
Mm, you smell good.

814
00:31:39,065 --> 00:31:42,034
Well so much for her being
released into your custody.

815
00:31:42,068 --> 00:31:44,003
We can't let him spend
too much time with Decker.

816
00:31:44,036 --> 00:31:45,404
She'll figure out
something's going on.

817
00:31:45,437 --> 00:31:47,473
(sighs) Let me see
what I can do.

818
00:31:57,616 --> 00:31:59,418
It's time for you
to go home, Abel.

819
00:31:59,451 --> 00:32:01,553
It wasn't easy for me
to track you down,

820
00:32:01,587 --> 00:32:03,922
but you're not getting away
from me this time.

821
00:32:06,058 --> 00:32:08,094
What the...

822
00:32:08,127 --> 00:32:11,497
MAZE: Meet my
punching bag.

823
00:32:11,530 --> 00:32:13,532
Look familiar?

824
00:32:13,565 --> 00:32:17,669
Mazikeen.
What are you doing here?

825
00:32:17,703 --> 00:32:20,006
What does it look like?

826
00:32:20,039 --> 00:32:22,208
Keeping you out
of Lucifer's way.

827
00:32:25,644 --> 00:32:26,445
(shouts)

828
00:32:26,478 --> 00:32:28,014
I don't want to
fight you, Mazikeen.

829
00:32:28,047 --> 00:32:30,983
Who cares what you want?

830
00:32:34,620 --> 00:32:36,622
So you worked here
for two years,

831
00:32:36,655 --> 00:32:37,456
it's still not ringing a bell?

832
00:32:37,489 --> 00:32:39,691
No, but your backside
is ringing a...

833
00:32:39,725 --> 00:32:41,193
Oh, you poor, forgetful thing.

834
00:32:41,227 --> 00:32:42,694
Thankfully, all we need
is your fingerprint.

835
00:32:42,728 --> 00:32:45,097
Well, my finger goes wherever
the lady tells me it goes.

836
00:32:45,131 --> 00:32:47,133
(phone ringing, vibrating)

837
00:32:47,166 --> 00:32:49,501
Hey, Dan. Did you have any
luck finding Bree's phone?

838
00:32:49,535 --> 00:32:50,702
DAN:
No.

839
00:32:50,736 --> 00:32:52,504
Because guess who collected
her stuff from the hospital?

840
00:32:52,538 --> 00:32:54,606
Alexa.

841
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:55,607
That's odd.

842
00:32:55,641 --> 00:32:56,475
Yeah, right?

843
00:32:56,508 --> 00:32:58,010
So, I dug deeper.

844
00:32:58,044 --> 00:32:59,611
Looked into her Pilates alibi.

845
00:32:59,645 --> 00:33:01,580
Get this: her class

846
00:33:01,613 --> 00:33:02,581
is actually in the morning.

847
00:33:02,614 --> 00:33:05,617
She rescheduled that day
for 2:00 p.m. exactly.

848
00:33:05,651 --> 00:33:07,686
It's like she knew to be
out of the office.

849
00:33:07,719 --> 00:33:09,121
She knew the bomb was coming.

850
00:33:09,155 --> 00:33:10,789
Who knew?
Alexa.

851
00:33:10,822 --> 00:33:12,624
What, and the Bolivians
warned her? Why?

852
00:33:12,658 --> 00:33:14,526
Put it on speakerphone.
(sighs)

853
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:17,663
Okay, maybe the Bolivians were
working with Alexa, not Bree.

854
00:33:17,696 --> 00:33:19,665
Maybe Bree found out
what they were up to

855
00:33:19,698 --> 00:33:20,732
and wanted to blow the whistle.

856
00:33:20,766 --> 00:33:22,534
Well, that would explain

857
00:33:22,568 --> 00:33:24,703
those incoming wires
in Bree's account.

858
00:33:24,736 --> 00:33:27,606
Cartel tried to pay her off,
silence her.

859
00:33:27,639 --> 00:33:29,208
And when the nice way
didn't work,

860
00:33:29,241 --> 00:33:30,442
they tried the not-so-nice way.

861
00:33:30,476 --> 00:33:33,745
Well, hopefully the proof is
behind drawer number one, so...

862
00:33:33,779 --> 00:33:34,746
Wait a minute.

863
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:36,648
Why would Alexa send us
straight to the place

864
00:33:36,682 --> 00:33:38,550
where we'd find proof
of her crimes?

865
00:33:38,584 --> 00:33:39,618
Makes no sense.

866
00:33:39,651 --> 00:33:41,187
Unless...

867
00:33:42,088 --> 00:33:43,689
...it's a trap.

868
00:33:44,723 --> 00:33:45,757
Bree, wait!

869
00:33:45,791 --> 00:33:47,526
(clicks, beeps)

870
00:33:50,129 --> 00:33:52,664
Don't move.

871
00:34:02,308 --> 00:34:03,409
DAN:
Alexa knew Bree would need proof

872
00:34:03,442 --> 00:34:05,744
to turn her in, so she must have
rigged the file cabinet

873
00:34:05,777 --> 00:34:07,579
that contained it.
We walked right into her trap.

874
00:34:07,613 --> 00:34:09,115
If they move,
the whole thing blows.

875
00:34:09,148 --> 00:34:10,549
Call the bomb squad.

876
00:34:10,582 --> 00:34:12,618
PIERCE: Decker, you need to get
out of there, stat.

877
00:34:12,651 --> 00:34:14,153
I'm not going anywhere,
Lieutenant.

878
00:34:14,186 --> 00:34:15,721
What do you mean,
you're not going anywhere?

879
00:34:15,754 --> 00:34:17,789
You need to get
out of there, now.

880
00:34:17,823 --> 00:34:19,725
Don't worry,
I'm staying right here.

881
00:34:19,758 --> 00:34:21,660
Oh, woman,
your loyalty touches me.

882
00:34:21,693 --> 00:34:23,129
PIERCE: What happened to
"You're the lieutenant,

883
00:34:23,162 --> 00:34:23,962
you call the shots"?

884
00:34:23,995 --> 00:34:25,731
CHLOE:
There is an innocent victim

885
00:34:25,764 --> 00:34:27,733
glued to a bomb.

886
00:34:27,766 --> 00:34:30,602
"Innocent victim"
is highly debatable.

887
00:34:30,636 --> 00:34:32,171
Lucifer, Bree was trying to do
the right thing.

888
00:34:32,204 --> 00:34:34,773
It's why the Bolivians
and Alexa want her dead.

889
00:34:34,806 --> 00:34:35,741
I'm not leaving.

890
00:34:35,774 --> 00:34:36,842
ABEL:
Oh, my flock

891
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,677
is your flock,
this I swear.

892
00:34:38,710 --> 00:34:39,778
PIERCE:
Okay.

893
00:34:39,811 --> 00:34:41,613
No, no, no, o-opposite of okay.

894
00:34:41,647 --> 00:34:43,749
PIERCE:
If you're gonna stay, Decker,

895
00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:44,883
I can talk you through
defusing it.

896
00:34:44,916 --> 00:34:46,585
It's safer
than waiting for it

897
00:34:46,618 --> 00:34:47,586
to blow up before the bomb squad
gets there...

898
00:34:47,619 --> 00:34:49,188
Wait a minute.
Wait, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

899
00:34:49,221 --> 00:34:51,190
Chloe, Chloe,
think about this, okay?

900
00:34:51,223 --> 00:34:52,724
Think about Trixie.

901
00:34:52,758 --> 00:34:54,793
I am thinking about her.

902
00:34:54,826 --> 00:34:57,596
And I'm also thinking
that Bree's a daughter, too.

903
00:34:57,629 --> 00:34:58,764
Oh, come on.

904
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:01,867
So...
(sighs)

905
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:04,303
...what do I do now? What,

906
00:35:04,336 --> 00:35:06,172
cut all these wires willy-nilly?

907
00:35:07,239 --> 00:35:08,807
Damn movies. No.

908
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:11,177
You have to get into the box
and disconnect the trigger.

909
00:35:11,210 --> 00:35:12,378
And, very carefully,

910
00:35:12,411 --> 00:35:13,812
remove the blasting cap.

911
00:35:13,845 --> 00:35:15,347
Ugh, this is madness.

912
00:35:15,381 --> 00:35:16,882
PIERCE:
Then toss it as far as possible.

913
00:35:16,915 --> 00:35:19,751
Oh, you want her to toss an
explosive, that sounds safe.

914
00:35:19,785 --> 00:35:22,654
If the cap goes off away from
the charge, it'll be harmless.

915
00:35:22,688 --> 00:35:25,257
Lieutenant!
I understand why your priority

916
00:35:25,291 --> 00:35:27,259
is to save your...

917
00:35:27,293 --> 00:35:29,328
this young woman, but I
will not let you endanger

918
00:35:29,361 --> 00:35:30,829
the detective's life
in the process.

919
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:32,631
He's not endangering my life.

920
00:35:32,664 --> 00:35:35,201
I am choosing to be here,
and if you're not gonna help,

921
00:35:35,234 --> 00:35:36,768
you should probably just leave.

922
00:35:36,802 --> 00:35:38,670
Well, we both know
I'm not gonna do that.

923
00:35:39,838 --> 00:35:41,840
I'm your partner.

924
00:35:44,343 --> 00:35:46,712
Okay, good.

925
00:35:46,745 --> 00:35:48,214
Then listen to me--
I'm gonna need both my hands,

926
00:35:48,247 --> 00:35:49,348
so please come help me.

927
00:35:49,381 --> 00:35:51,350
Okay? Hold this.

928
00:35:53,452 --> 00:35:55,687
I'll use this,
and, uh...

929
00:35:55,721 --> 00:35:56,855
All right.

930
00:35:58,724 --> 00:36:00,726
(bomb beeping)

931
00:36:00,759 --> 00:36:02,794
(quietly):
Easy...

932
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:06,932
CHLOE:
Got the blasting cap.

933
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,735
And...

934
00:36:13,772 --> 00:36:15,841
Okay.

935
00:36:15,874 --> 00:36:19,811
I think that means you can
take your thumb off now.

936
00:36:19,845 --> 00:36:21,313
(beeps)

937
00:36:21,347 --> 00:36:22,414
All right.

938
00:36:22,448 --> 00:36:23,849
And don't tell us

939
00:36:23,882 --> 00:36:25,451
where you want to put it next.

940
00:36:25,484 --> 00:36:26,852
MAZE:
Up your butt!

941
00:36:26,885 --> 00:36:29,221
(panting)

942
00:36:29,255 --> 00:36:30,789
That's where I want
to shove this.

943
00:36:30,822 --> 00:36:34,360
And then, I'll press the button.

944
00:36:34,393 --> 00:36:36,462
I don't even understand
why you're so angry.

945
00:36:36,495 --> 00:36:39,365
So what if Linda and I
got together?

946
00:36:40,832 --> 00:36:43,769
You dumped me.

947
00:36:43,802 --> 00:36:45,704
Remember?

948
00:36:45,737 --> 00:36:48,240
No, it's not about that.

949
00:36:48,274 --> 00:36:50,776
Okay? It's about the betrayal.

950
00:36:50,809 --> 00:36:51,810
The dirty...

951
00:36:52,811 --> 00:36:53,879
...sneaky...

952
00:36:55,781 --> 00:36:56,748
...lies!

953
00:36:56,782 --> 00:36:57,949
When will
you understand

954
00:36:57,983 --> 00:37:00,952
that we were trying
to protect you?

955
00:37:00,986 --> 00:37:03,789
And when will you understand
I don't believe you?

956
00:37:03,822 --> 00:37:06,858
(sighs)

957
00:37:06,892 --> 00:37:07,826
All right.

958
00:37:10,296 --> 00:37:11,430
Fine.

959
00:37:15,801 --> 00:37:19,338
(both panting)

960
00:37:19,371 --> 00:37:21,840
Well, come on!

961
00:37:21,873 --> 00:37:24,776
Come on! It's no fun
if you just stand there!

962
00:37:24,810 --> 00:37:26,312
It's about as much fun
as watching you

963
00:37:26,345 --> 00:37:28,280
break Linda's heart, I'd say.

964
00:37:28,314 --> 00:37:29,815
(yells)

965
00:37:31,350 --> 00:37:33,885
(grunts)

966
00:37:33,919 --> 00:37:37,323
Even this, you had to ruin.

967
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:49,435
(door opens, closes)

968
00:37:49,468 --> 00:37:50,869
(police radio chatter)

969
00:37:50,902 --> 00:37:53,805
Okay, thank you.

970
00:37:53,839 --> 00:37:55,073
Hi.

971
00:37:55,106 --> 00:37:56,475
So, we were able to lift

972
00:37:56,508 --> 00:37:58,544
one of Alexa's prints
from the explosive.

973
00:37:58,577 --> 00:37:59,911
Oh, good.

974
00:37:59,945 --> 00:38:01,480
Sounds like enough
to arrest her for murder.

975
00:38:01,513 --> 00:38:03,048
And get her to flip
on the Bolivians.

976
00:38:03,081 --> 00:38:04,883
Apparently, she was using
her movies to launder money

977
00:38:04,916 --> 00:38:06,352
for the cartel.

978
00:38:06,385 --> 00:38:08,086
And that's what Bree
was trying to expose.

979
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:11,323
Shame. I mean, I had the perfect
title for The Plunge 2.

980
00:38:12,591 --> 00:38:13,825
2 Deep 2 Plunge.

981
00:38:13,859 --> 00:38:14,993
With the number two, each time,

982
00:38:15,026 --> 00:38:16,094
instead of... the word.
Instead of the word.

983
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:17,363
(both chuckle)
Yeah, I get it.

984
00:38:17,396 --> 00:38:18,430
It's funny.

985
00:38:18,464 --> 00:38:19,898
Yeah.
Yeah.

986
00:38:19,931 --> 00:38:21,367
So...

987
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:22,801
(clears throat)

988
00:38:22,834 --> 00:38:24,570
...I just wanted
to say thank you, again.

989
00:38:26,505 --> 00:38:28,374
I couldn't have done it
without you.

990
00:38:29,941 --> 00:38:31,943
Night.

991
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:37,516
Without me...

992
00:38:37,549 --> 00:38:42,087
you wouldn't have been in danger
in the first place.

993
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:46,492
CHARLOTTE:
I'm sorry about last time.

994
00:38:46,525 --> 00:38:48,594
I'm a bit of a control freak.

995
00:38:48,627 --> 00:38:49,861
Ah.

996
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:50,896
Really?

997
00:38:50,929 --> 00:38:51,930
I hadn't noticed.

998
00:38:51,963 --> 00:38:53,965
(chuckles softly)

999
00:38:53,999 --> 00:38:54,966
So, what's changed?

1000
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,935
Well, I realized

1001
00:38:56,968 --> 00:38:59,037
that you're right,
you're the expert.

1002
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:02,007
And I should
trust you.

1003
00:39:02,040 --> 00:39:05,544
And as scary as that is...
(sighs)

1004
00:39:05,577 --> 00:39:07,078
...there's something
much scarier.

1005
00:39:09,448 --> 00:39:12,451
I, um, I wake up...

1006
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:15,954
...smell coffee.

1007
00:39:15,987 --> 00:39:16,922
It's nice.

1008
00:39:16,955 --> 00:39:18,056
I have breakfast

1009
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:19,525
with my family.

1010
00:39:19,558 --> 00:39:21,427
Uh, we're happy.

1011
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:23,962
(chuckles)

1012
00:39:23,995 --> 00:39:25,030
At peace.

1013
00:39:25,063 --> 00:39:26,932
And then, a man

1014
00:39:26,965 --> 00:39:29,901
walks in
and shoots each of them.

1015
00:39:29,935 --> 00:39:31,102
Dead.

1016
00:39:31,136 --> 00:39:34,873
And I know this man because he's
somebody that I represented,

1017
00:39:34,906 --> 00:39:38,477
and I know that he should be
in jail, but he's not.

1018
00:39:40,479 --> 00:39:41,947
Because of me.

1019
00:39:45,050 --> 00:39:46,952
I just smile,

1020
00:39:46,985 --> 00:39:50,055
while my family is killed.

1021
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:54,926
I don't move a muscle.

1022
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:57,095
(shuddering breath)

1023
00:39:57,128 --> 00:39:59,931
Because I'm the reason
that it's happening.

1024
00:39:59,965 --> 00:40:02,300
I'm the reason that he's free.

1025
00:40:06,171 --> 00:40:08,640
And then, I wake up.

1026
00:40:08,674 --> 00:40:12,010
It's a new morning.

1027
00:40:12,043 --> 00:40:14,179
I smell the same coffee.

1028
00:40:16,214 --> 00:40:19,451
Pour the same cereal.

1029
00:40:19,485 --> 00:40:23,154
And then, someone else walks in,

1030
00:40:23,188 --> 00:40:25,457
and shoots my family.

1031
00:40:27,493 --> 00:40:30,228
This time,
it's a different person.

1032
00:40:30,261 --> 00:40:33,465
Someone else I set free.

1033
00:40:40,171 --> 00:40:42,474
And I just...

1034
00:40:42,508 --> 00:40:45,944
smile again.

1035
00:40:45,977 --> 00:40:48,980
And I die inside again.

1036
00:40:49,014 --> 00:40:52,050
Over and over, and...

1037
00:40:55,286 --> 00:41:00,025
I don't know what it'll take
to stay out of that place.

1038
00:41:03,061 --> 00:41:06,164
I'm trying my best.

1039
00:41:06,197 --> 00:41:09,200
But I don't know
if it'll be enough.

1040
00:41:13,071 --> 00:41:17,643
Well, it's a very brave start.

1041
00:41:19,044 --> 00:41:22,047
* I don't believe in Satan

1042
00:41:25,551 --> 00:41:27,152
* But he believes in me...

1043
00:41:29,788 --> 00:41:32,190
Thank you
for saving my life, Kane.

1044
00:41:32,223 --> 00:41:35,160
I suppose we're even now.

1045
00:41:35,193 --> 00:41:36,094
(sighs)

1046
00:41:36,127 --> 00:41:38,029
Yet, this is still there.

1047
00:41:38,063 --> 00:41:39,130
Hmm.

1048
00:41:39,164 --> 00:41:41,800
This whole time, you've been
in a kind of Hell, too.

1049
00:41:43,669 --> 00:41:46,204
You still are.

1050
00:41:46,237 --> 00:41:48,006
I'm sorry.

1051
00:41:48,039 --> 00:41:49,775
I'm sorry, too, brother.

1052
00:41:49,808 --> 00:41:52,177
(exhales)

1053
00:41:52,210 --> 00:41:55,714
Your face is still
the face of my torturer.

1054
00:41:55,747 --> 00:41:57,716
Fair enough.

1055
00:41:57,749 --> 00:41:59,284
I guess we still
need some space.

1056
00:41:59,317 --> 00:42:02,588
That, we can agree on.

1057
00:42:02,621 --> 00:42:05,023
* He's the master of deceit

1058
00:42:05,056 --> 00:42:08,293
* I don't believe in Satan...

1059
00:42:08,326 --> 00:42:11,563
Ah, that was
quite civil, actually.

1060
00:42:13,131 --> 00:42:15,133
I know I promised to help you
end your curse,

1061
00:42:15,166 --> 00:42:19,771
but I'm afraid we need
to dissolve our unholy alliance.

1062
00:42:19,805 --> 00:42:22,674
Why?

1063
00:42:22,708 --> 00:42:25,143
The risk is too great.

1064
00:42:25,176 --> 00:42:27,045
I mean, I don't mind
putting myself in danger,

1065
00:42:27,078 --> 00:42:28,213
but the detective?

1066
00:42:29,615 --> 00:42:32,818
If she had died,
it would have been my fault.

1067
00:42:32,851 --> 00:42:35,253
But you're the Devil,
you always keep your word.

1068
00:42:35,286 --> 00:42:36,487
I do.

1069
00:42:36,521 --> 00:42:40,258
So I hope you understand how
difficult a decision this was.

1070
00:42:40,291 --> 00:42:44,195
And yet, oddly,
the easiest I've ever made.

1071
00:42:47,132 --> 00:42:49,267
Well, I'm not done.

1072
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:52,604
Abel's how my curse started,
he's got to be the way it ends.

1073
00:42:52,638 --> 00:42:55,073
As long as he's alive,
I still have hope.

1074
00:42:55,106 --> 00:42:56,241
(tires screech)

1075
00:42:57,709 --> 00:42:59,177
(Kane sighs)

1076
00:42:59,210 --> 00:43:01,146
(chuckles)

1077
00:43:02,180 --> 00:43:03,214
(siren wailing)

1078
00:43:03,248 --> 00:43:06,184
No!

